x\in[0,\infty)
\{a_{n}\}_{n\in\mathbb N}
\{b_{n}\}_{n\in\mathbb N}
\lim_{n\to\infty}\left(\dfrac{1}{a_{n}+1}+\dfrac{1}{a_{n}+2}+\cdots+\dfrac{1}{a_{n}+b_{n}}\right)=x.
\lim_{n\to\infty}\dfrac{1}{n+1}+\dfrac{1}{n+2}+\cdots+\dfrac{1}{n+n}=\ln{2}
k_n
\ell_n
 \ln (\tfrac{\ell}{k}-\tfrac{1}{n})< \frac{1}{kn+1}+\frac{1}{kn+2}+\cdots+\frac{1}{\ell n}<\ln (\tfrac{\ell}{k}) 
 \frac{\ell_n}{k_n}\to\mathrm{e}^x. 
 \lim_{n\to\infty}\sum_{j=1}^{(\ell_m-k_m)n} \frac{1}{k_nn+j}\to x. 
